**CASE HEARD BY JUDGE BOROWSKI FOR JUDGE CONEN**

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by the state, defense and defendant.  Additional statement from Aaron Q.
 
COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence with credit for 26 days. 
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS.  
The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION (if revoked):
*Serve 9 months in the House of Correction, consecutive, straight time; NO RELEASE PRIVILEGES.  Good time allowed, HOC work assignments allowed.  NO ELECTRONIC MONITIORING;
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Meet with agent monthly;
*Cooperate with random urine screens- DOC to test at least 1x per month (or more);
*Obtain employment and /or school equal to 40 hrs per week;
*Obtain high school diploma, GED or HSED;
*Perform 50 hours of community service;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

 If revoked, the Court ordered all financial obligations to be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.

Defendant is informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms or body armor.
Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated.  
Defendant advised of his right to appeal this matter.
